## Validate changes (fast defaults)

- Prefer fast checks over production builds.
- Don’t start/stop dev servers unless explicitly asked; assume the developer runs them.

### Default workflow

- Prefer running autofix first:
  - backend: `make fix-backend`
  - frontend: `make fix-frontend`
- Then run typechecks when relevant:
  - `make types-all` (or `make types-frontend`)

### What “lint” means here

- `make lint-frontend` runs `biome check` (verifies format + lint, no writes).
- `make lint-backend` runs Ruff checks + format `--check` (no writes).
- After `make fix-all`, running `make lint-all` is usually redundant (it should already pass), but it’s fine as a verification step.

### Tests

- Default:
  - `make test-backend`
- Run E2E only when UI/API/map behavior changes:
  - `make test-e2e-frontend` (or `cd frontend && E2E_FAST=1 E2E_REUSE_ONLY=1 npm run -s e2e`)
- Only run `cd frontend && npm run -s build` when bundling/deps/config changed or build-only failures appear.

### Optional: Project AIDA (if available)

If a “Project AIDA” MCP server is available in this environment, prefer using it to streamline routine developer workflow (issue/PR hygiene, checklists, release notes). Keep usage optional since it may not be present everywhere.

